# Ports and Adapters

## Invariant

Domain depends on **ports** (ABC/Protocol); infrastructure implements **adapters**.

## Where things live

| Type | Location | Example |
|------|----------|---------|
| Port | `cortex_core/ports/` | `AlfrescoPort`, `SearchPort` |
| Shared infra | `cortex_core/infrastructure/` | Redis, Weaviate client |
| Stub/prod adapter | `cortex_connectors/` | `StubAlfrescoClient` |
| Module wrapper | `module_*/adapters/` | `WeaviateSearchStore` |

## SearchPort ownership

- **Read**: `module-ai` (`search_chunks`)
- **Write**: `module-ingestion` (`upsert_document_chunks`)
- Shared DTO: `ChunkHit` in the port

## External systems

| System | Port | Connector |
|--------|------|-----------|
| Alfresco/DMS | `AlfrescoPort` | `cortex_connectors.alfresco` |
| Blob/S3 | `BlobPort` | `cortex_connectors.blob` |
| OCR | `OCRPort` | `cortex_connectors.ocr` |
| LLM | `LLMPort` | `cortex_core.infrastructure.llm` |

New external system: port in core → adapter in connectors → use in module.

## Do not put in cortex-core

ORM models, FastAPI routes, Celery tasks, feature business rules, agent prompts.

